## Contract Anchoring

Every function must carry an `expect:` + `[P{N}]` contract annotation that links it to a functional requirement. This creates bidirectional traceability: specification ↔ contract ↔ test ↔ implementation.

The contract format is:
```
/// expect: "<user's functional expectation in their own voice>"
/// [P{N}] Motivating: <principle name> — <why this contract exists>
/// pre:  <what must be true before calling>
/// post: <what the function guarantees after returning>
/// inv:  <what must always hold across operations> (optional, for types)
/// [P{N}] Constraining: <principle name> — <what the code cannot do>
/// prob: p=<threshold>, δ=<tolerance>, k=<recovery window> (only for non-deterministic functions per Testing Discipline §7.6)
```

