{% if test_style == "fuzz" %}
## Test Style: Fuzz

For `pub fn` input surfaces accepting arbitrary data from external sources (Testing Discipline §2.4, T6).

Contract preconditions: implicit precondition = "any input" — no `prop_assume!` filtering.
Contract postcondition: "does not panic" — verify via `catch_unwind` + proptest with unlimited input generation.

```rust
// expect: "The function does not panic on any input"
#[test]
fn fuzz_input_surface_does_not_panic() {
    proptest!(|(input in any::<Vec<u8>>())| {
        let result = std::panic::catch_unwind(|| target_function(&input));
        prop_assert!(result.is_ok(), "function panicked on input: {:?}", input);
    });
}
```

Fuzz tests live in `tests/` directory at crate root. No `prop_assume!` — accept all inputs.

{% elif test_style == "system" %}
## Test Style: System (E2E)

For cross-crate end-to-end workflows spanning multiple `pub fn` boundaries (Testing Discipline §2.4).

Write a single integration test in `tests/` that exercises the full vertical slice. Contracts chain through the call stack — testing `f` transitively verifies `g`'s contracts.

```rust
// End-to-end workflow test for the system boundary
#[tokio::test]
async fn system_end_to_end_workflow() {
    // Bootstrap dependencies, exercise full vertical slice, verify side effects
}
```

System tests use `hkask-test-harness` for database/filesystem fixtures. The test verifies observable outcomes at the system boundary, not internal intermediate states.

